## Usage

{% if design.transport == "http" %}
### As an MCP server (HTTP transport)

```bash
mcp-{{ design.server_name | kebab_case }}
```

The server starts on `http://{{ design.http_host }}:{{ design.http_port }}` by default.

Override with environment variables:

```bash
MCP_HOST=0.0.0.0 MCP_PORT=9000 mcp-{{ design.server_name | kebab_case }}
```

### MCP client configuration

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "{{ design.server_name }}": {
      "url": "http://localhost:{{ design.http_port }}/sse"
    }
  }
}
```

### Docker

```bash
docker build -t mcp-{{ design.server_name | kebab_case }} .
docker run -p {{ design.http_port }}:{{ design.http_port }} mcp-{{ design.server_name | kebab_case }}
```
{% else %}
### As an MCP server (stdio transport)

```bash
mcp-{{ design.server_name | kebab_case }}
```

### Claude Desktop configuration

Add to your `claude_desktop_config.json`:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "{{ design.server_name }}": {
      "command": "mcp-{{ design.server_name | kebab_case }}"
    }
  }
}
```
